text: Daphnella degrangei is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Raphitomidae.Worldwide Mollusc Species Data Base: Daphnella degrangei ==Description== The length of the shell attains 11 mm. ==Distribution== Fossils of this marine species were found in Miocene strata in Aquitaine, France. ==References== * Cossmann, Maurice. Sur quelques formes nouvelles ou peu connues des faluns du Bordelais... Au secrétariat de l'Association, 1894. ==External links== * Fossilshells.nl: Daphnella degrangei degrangei Category:Gastropods described in 1894
title: Daphnella degrangei
